{"id": 225007232, "title": "Doireann Garrihy responds to people who say her relationship with Mark has moved 'quite fast", "text": "Doireann Garrihy says \"when you know you know\" after meeting and getting engaged to her fianc\u00e9 Mark Mehigan. She responded to people who suggested their relationship has moved \"quite fast\". She joked that they still see each other's flaws even though they are in a love bubble. The couple first met in October 2022 and Mark got down on bended knee to pop the question in a pre-Christmas engagement in November 2023. Read more: Doireann Garrihy holds back tears as she discusses her 'gut feeling' to leave 2FM Read more: The 2 Johnnies share real reason behind shock 2FM exit: 'It's not as juicy as people want it to be' Doireann said: \"Oh no, we definitely see flaws in each other and I think living together kinda puts the magnifying glass up to that, as well. We only met in October '22 so I think people would probably look on and think 'That's quite fast' but, without wanting to be too cringe or clich\u00e9 about it, when you know, you know! \"We've both seen a lot and done a lot and we both met at a time that's right for each other.\" For Doireann, the day of her engagement was the happiest day of her life. She told VIP Magazine: \"It was such a warm day, such a lovely time of year as well. It was the 30th of November, the first weekend of true Christmas buzz in Dublin. \"We went into town and got together with family and friends and it was heavenly. All our festive plans turned into extra engagement celebrations. \"Then it was straight into Dancing With The Stars. I got engaged on a Thursday and I was back to work on the Monday and it was like, 'Does anybody even know I'm engaged?!' [laughing] Both Doireann and Mark are known for their comedy skills, so it is no surprise they roast each other and have banter at home The Dancing with the Stars co-presenter said: \"Of course, we do! Is that not the foundation of all lasting relationships? [Laughs] Mark has the quickest, sharpest wit I have ever come across, he can out-funny anyone in a room. \"I listen to his podcast The Weekly Roast and have to pause it repeatedly because there are jokes within jokes within jokes. He is a gifted comedian. \"He leaves the impersonations to me\u2026his South Dublin accent can't quite stretch any further than Ballsbridge!\" Join RSVP Live's WhatsApp community to get celebrity news and our top stories", "summary": "The podcaster and radio presenter revealed that she and her fianc\u00e9 Mark Mehigan both met at a time that was right for each other - she also lifts the lid on their life at home", "url": "https://www.rsvplive.ie/news/celebs/doireann-garrihy-responds-people-who-32915224", "image": "https://i2-prod.rsvplive.ie/news/celebs/article32914674.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_Doireann-Garrihy-Mark-Mehigan.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 12:07:35", "author": "Mikie O'loughlin", "authors": ["Mikie O'loughlin"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ie", "sentiment": 0.38}